{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Embedding vector dimensionality matches the vector index dimension for a query.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"The failure is typically a real boundary mismatch between configured embedding model output and the live vector DB index schema; mocks can hide model/version/config drift that only appears with a real embedding API call and real index metadata.","test_description":"Run the API against a real embedding endpoint and real vector index, submit a query, capture produced embedding length (or embedding metadata), and assert it equals the index dimension; fail on any mismatch before similarity search.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.08,"Integration":0.24,"System":0.64,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Similarity search results are ordered by descending cosine similarity.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"This behavior is about actual retrieval ordering from the vector search component; wiring/config issues (metric type, score interpretation, sort direction) are often only visible with the real vector engine, which mocks can mask.","test_description":"Seed a real vector DB index with controlled vectors, execute search through the API path, and assert returned scores are monotonically non-increasing and correspond to cosine similarity ordering.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.06,"Integration":0.31,"System":0.58,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"LLM re-ranking changes ordering for nuanced-intent queries versus raw similarity ranking.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on semantic judgment from a real LLM and may vary across runs/prompts; deterministic mocks cannot validate whether nuanced intent causes meaningful reordering.","test_description":"Use a nuanced query and a fixed candidate set from similarity search, call the real re-ranking LLM multiple times, and verify that in at least some runs the final order differs from raw vector ranking while remaining relevant to the query intent.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.03,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.82,"Workflow":0.06}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"Queries with no close matches return an empty set, not low-relevance noise.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The key failure boundary is local module interaction: score thresholding/business rules applied to similarity results. This can be caught by wiring embed/search/threshold logic together with controlled data; full external infra is helpful but not strictly minimal.","test_description":"Populate a test index with unrelated items, run query through integrated embedding+search+threshold path, and assert the API returns an empty list when all scores are below the configured cutoff.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.56,"System":0.27,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"Median end-to-end query latency remains under 2 seconds.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Latency is an end-to-end operational property across real HTTP/service boundaries (API, embedding service, vector DB, reranker). Mocked dependencies understate latency and hide real bottlenecks.","test_description":"Execute a representative load scenario against the running service with real downstream dependencies, collect end-to-end response times, compute median over sufficient samples, and assert p50 < 2.0s.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.1,"System":0.83,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.03}}]}
